CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1962, pg. 24, reads: "Echo of Gay Nineties - This antique horseless carriage might not be the fastest mode of transportation, but at least it's a cool one for James Dyer, sales official for the Iron City Beer Co. Here the classical-togged gent is shown on a jaunt through the city."
TitMainTitle: James Dyer driving horseless carriage with Iron City Beer logos down street with KQV Radio 14 billboard in background
